\fs18 \cf4 \cb31 \strokec4 Night falls dark as ink, the stars shining bright and brilliant.\cb1 \
\cb31 She journeys from afar, carrying stories, ballads, and unfinished verses.\cb1 \
\cb31 She plucks a flower, dew gathered upon its petals, and sets it on the windowsill.\cb1 \
\cb31 She watches over your dreams, keeping them warm and safe.\cb1 \
\
\cb31 "Good morning... Huh? When did you get here, Lucia?"\cb1 \
\cb31 "I'm not sure, but it hasn't been too long... time just seems to fly when I'm around you, Proxy."\cb1 \
